# Feature Spec: Film-Review Registration UI

## 1. Feature Overview

Create a registration experience inside the Film-Review Angular app (`/login/film-review`) that is visually and behaviorally aligned with the current login page, while reusing existing backend contracts.

Goal:
- move registration from legacy standalone page (`/login/register.html`) into Film-Review route/template flow
- keep existing servlet and REST endpoints as contract baseline
- avoid breaking current login/session/HMAC behavior

Primary source files:
- `dalogin-quarkus/src/main/resources/META-INF/resources/film-review/app.js`
- `dalogin-quarkus/src/main/resources/META-INF/resources/film-review/templates/login.html`
- `dalogin-quarkus/src/main/resources/META-INF/resources/register.html`
- `dalogin-quarkus/src/main/resources/META-INF/resources/film-review/jsR/register.js`

Primary backend owners:
- `dalogin-quarkus` (registration, voucher, activation)
- `mbook-quarkus` (username/email precheck)

---

## 2. Scope

## Included
- New Film-Review route and template for registration UI (same visual style family as login).
- Angular controller/service wiring for registration flow using existing endpoints.
- Username and email availability checks using existing `mbook` endpoints.
- Registration submit flow using existing `dalogin` servlet endpoint(s).
- Route-level navigation link updates from login to registration inside Film-Review app.
- Error/success rendering compatible with current servlet JSON and status behavior.

## Excluded
- Rewriting auth stack, servlet architecture, or HMAC algorithm.
- Replacing legacy endpoints with new contracts.
- Account profile completion, social login, captcha, or OTP redesign.
- Activation redesign beyond using current `activation` endpoint contract.

---

## 3. Functional Requirements

### REQ-REG-1 Film-Review route
Add a Film-Review Angular route for registration (recommended: `#/register`) with template under `film-review/templates`.

### REQ-REG-2 UI parity with login
Registration page must follow login page styling and layout conventions:
- hero/header style
- centered form card (`login-wrap` style family)
- same button and alert visual language

### REQ-REG-3 Required form fields
Registration UI must capture:
- username
- email
- password
- voucher (if required by selected endpoint mode)

### REQ-REG-4 Precheck username
On registration form interaction, call:
- `GET /mbook-1/rest/newuser/{newuser}`
Trigger rule:
- Fire username availability check when input length reaches at least 2 characters.
Interpretation:
- `200` => username available
- `412` => username already taken

### REQ-REG-5 Precheck email
On registration form interaction, call:
- `GET /mbook-1/rest/newemail/{newemail}`
Trigger rule:
- Fire email availability check only when a full email value is present (valid full address format, e.g. `name@example.com`).
Interpretation:
- `200` => email available
- `412` => email already taken

### REQ-REG-5A Precheck UX behavior
Registration UI must provide clear precheck UX states for username/email checks:
- show threshold/format hint before a request is eligible (`username < 2 chars`, invalid/incomplete email)
- show `checking` state while async availability request is in-flight
- show `available`, `taken`, or `unknown` result state after response
- debounce precheck requests during typing to reduce noisy repeated calls

### REQ-REG-5B Form validation state + submit gating
Validation responses for username/email availability must update the form state directly (inline field feedback), not only global dialogs.

Submit button behavior:
- must remain disabled until all required values are valid
- required valid state includes: username length threshold met, username available, full valid email format, email available, password present, and voucher present when voucher mode is enabled
- must remain disabled while username/email precheck is in `checking` state

### REQ-REG-6 Voucher validation (voucher mode)
If voucher mode is enabled in UI, validate voucher before submit using:
- `POST /login/voucher`

### REQ-REG-7 Registration submit
Registration submit must use existing servlet contract:
- primary: `POST /login/register`
- optional mode: `POST /login/registerWithoutVoucher`

Payload and headers must match existing servlet expectations (`user`, `pswrd`, `email`, `deviceId`, optional `voucher_`, HMAC headers).

### REQ-REG-8 Activation handling
Registration success path must support activation behavior already provided by:
- `GET /login/activation?activation=...`
- `POST /login/activation` (resend/trigger path where applicable)

### REQ-REG-9 Navigation integration
Replace login page registration link target from legacy static page (`/login/register.html`) to Film-Review route (`#/register`).

### REQ-REG-10 Error mapping
UI must handle existing response patterns without contract changes:
- `200` success
- `300` activation-related response behavior where present
- `412` precondition failures (availability/voucher)
- `502` registration failure

### REQ-REG-11 Session/token behavior
On successful registration response carrying `X-Token`, preserve current session/token storage approach used by Film-Review login flow.

### REQ-REG-12 Source-of-truth rule
If docs and code differ, endpoint behavior must follow running code in servlets/controllers.

### REQ-REG-13 Registration dialog state matrix
Registration UI must define and use explicit dialog/alert states for voucher and activation flows.

Required dialog keys and trigger conditions:
- `REG_VOUCHER_INVALID`: voucher check fails (`POST /login/voucher` returns precondition/error)
- `REG_VOUCHER_VALID`: voucher check succeeds
- `REG_ACTIVATION_REQUIRED`: registration returns activation-pending flow (`300` where applicable)
- `REG_ACTIVATION_EMAIL_SENT`: activation email sent successfully
- `REG_ACTIVATION_RESEND_SUCCESS`: activation resend (`POST /login/activation`) succeeds
- `REG_ACTIVATION_RESEND_FAILED`: activation resend fails
- `REG_REGISTRATION_SUCCESS`: registration completed (`200` success path)
- `REG_REGISTRATION_FAILED`: registration submit fails (`502` or contract error)

Dialog rendering rules:
- Dialog text must be user-friendly and non-technical.
- Dialog style must reuse Film-Review alert/notification style already used on login/change-password pages.
- Dialogs must not expose sensitive details (password/hash/token/internal exception text).

### REQ-REG-14 Activation email CTA
When activation is required, UI must provide an explicit CTA to resend activation email using existing endpoint contract:
- `POST /login/activation`

CTA must be visible only in activation-pending state and hidden on fully successful registration state.

### REQ-REG-15 Activation-gated auth access
Until activation is confirmed, the user must not be able to access activation-protected auth/business endpoints after login.

Behavior rule:
- The UI must not hard-block the user preemptively.
- At the moment a protected request is made, backend response is source of truth.
- If activation is still pending, server returns activation-required response (existing `300` behavior where applicable), and UI **must** respond by showing the `REG_ACTIVATION_REQUIRED` dialog (warn style) along with the activation-resend CTA.
- This dialog must appear whenever activation is pending — both immediately after registration and whenever a protected request returns an activation-gating response during a later session.

This rule applies only to endpoint access control and response handling; no separate client-side activation state authority should be introduced.

---

## 4. Endpoint Contract Matrix (Registration)

| Step | Method | Path | Owner | Auth/HMAC expectation | Current status |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| Username check | GET | `/mbook-1/rest/newuser/{newuser}` | `mbook-quarkus` | session context, no registration-specific HMAC | implemented |
| Email check | GET | `/mbook-1/rest/newemail/{newemail}` | `mbook-quarkus` | session context, no registration-specific HMAC | implemented |
| Voucher check | POST | `/login/voucher` | `dalogin-quarkus` | current servlet validation | implemented |
| Register (voucher) | POST | `/login/register` | `dalogin-quarkus` | servlet expects registration HMAC headers + form body | implemented |
| Register (no voucher) | POST | `/login/registerWithoutVoucher` | `dalogin-quarkus` | servlet expects registration HMAC headers + form body | implemented |
| Activation link | GET | `/login/activation?activation=...` | `dalogin-quarkus` | tokenized activation payload | implemented |
| Activation resend | POST | `/login/activation` | `dalogin-quarkus` | session/token dependent | implemented |

---

## 5. Non-Functional Requirements

### REQ-REG-NF-1 Route consistency
Use plain hash routing conventions already used by Film-Review (`#/...`, not `#!/...`).

### REQ-REG-NF-2 UI consistency
Do not introduce a separate design system; reuse existing Film-Review styles and structure.

### REQ-REG-NF-3 Backward compatibility
Legacy `/login/register.html` may remain temporarily, but Film-Review flow is the primary path.

### REQ-REG-NF-4 Safety
Do not log raw password or sensitive registration fields in browser console.

### REQ-REG-NF-5 Maintainability
Registration controller logic should live in Film-Review app (`app.js` or modularized equivalent) with clear endpoint mapping.

---

## 6. Deliverables

- New Film-Review registration template (`film-review/templates/...`).
- New Angular route/controller wiring for registration in Film-Review app.
- Login template link update to Film-Review registration route.
- Endpoint mapping notes in WebUI docs/speckit artifacts.

---

## 7. Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Film-Review provides a registration route and template similar to login styling.
- [ ] Username precheck works via `/mbook-1/rest/newuser/{newuser}` with correct UI feedback.
- [ ] Email precheck works via `/mbook-1/rest/newemail/{newemail}` with correct UI feedback.
- [ ] Registration submit works against existing servlet endpoint(s) without backend contract change.
- [ ] Voucher mode (if enabled) validates via `/login/voucher` before submit.
- [ ] Login page registration link points to Film-Review route, not legacy static page.
- [ ] Success and error responses (`200/300/412/502`) are handled with user-visible messages.
- [ ] No sensitive registration values are written to browser logs.
- [ ] Voucher and activation flows show explicit dialogs (`invalid`, `pending`, `sent`, `resend success/fail`).
- [ ] Activation-pending state provides resend CTA wired to `POST /login/activation`.
- [ ] Dialog text does not expose sensitive/internal error content.
- [ ] Activation-pending users are denied access to activation-protected endpoints until activation is confirmed.
- [ ] UI does not pre-block access; it reacts to server activation-required response on protected request.
- [ ] Username precheck starts when username input has at least 2 characters.
- [ ] Email precheck fires only when a full email address is entered.
- [ ] Precheck UX states (`checking`, `available`, `taken`, `unknown`) and threshold/format hints are shown.
- [ ] Username/email precheck calls are debounced during typing.
- [ ] Username/email validation responses update inline field state in the form.
- [ ] Registration submit button stays disabled until all required values are valid and prechecks are not in-flight.
